  the  agriculture  sector  of  india  is  struggling  at different levels  we have placed agriculture sector on the backburner in our bid to add  much  importance  to  make  in  india  digital  india  and  startup    india    the government vehemently says that it will double the income of the farmers but it is a matter of sorrow that the incidents of suicides by the farmers are being reported almost from  every state  it is high time that we must think as seriously about the agriculture sector and the farmers as the manufacturing units industries and other service sectors  the total allocation for a very important scheme of the agriculture sector namely national agriculture development scheme has been slashed  from rs9594  crore  in  201314  to  rs4750  crore  in  201718    the  government  has introduced  organic  value  chain  development  for  north  eastern  states  and  for  the year 201516 a sum of rs133 crore was provided for it  this year this allocation has been reduced by rs100 crore  the government will have to take care of the people living in north east states also   the government needs to open a national organic  farming  institute  and  also  a  veterinary  college  in  arunachal  pradesh  when the government says that it will waive off the loans of farmers then i would like to ask whether arunachal pradesh or north eastern states or other states of the country  are  not  the  part  of  india    the  government  should  therefore  give  an assurance that it will waive off the loans of farmers of these states also this time    